issue.title: Inconsistency between stable versions of mods and post-processing after latest push

labels.name: triage
labels.description: This issue needs to be labeled

issue.body:
### Mod source

Factorio Mod Portal

### Operating system

>=Windows 10

### What kind of issue is this?

- [x] Compatibility
- [ ] Locale (names, descriptions, unknown keys)
- [ ] Graphical
- [x] Crash
- [ ] Progression
- [ ] Balance
- [ ] Pypostprocessing failure
- [ ] Other

### What is the problem?

After the latest push, the stable branch seems to have botched dependencies.

The recommended versions for Alien Life and Coal Processing require Pypostprocessing >= 3.0.28, which itself requires the beta branch of Factorio. The rest does manage to get updated, but then crash.

### Steps to reproduce

1. Run Factorio stable (2.0.47)
2. Try to update the mods to their latest versions via mod manager

### Additional context

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/f07bfaaf-490f-4251-9f4e-f42b2310f3af)

Attempt at updating

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/dd15d297-01bb-4874-802a-867582eb4299)

The crash

### Log file

[factorio-current.log](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/20542734/factorio-current.log)

issue.title: Create Toggle Button for Website Styling
issue.body:
As a user, I want to be able to choose the style (Day VS Night) of the website I am viewing by pressing a button/slide, so that I can read and enjoy learning about the company in a way I am more comfortable with. 

AC: Given the user slides/clicks on the toggle button, the website style will switch from Day VS Night Mode. 

**Day Mode:** this will be similar to "light" mode. It will be a lighter background image. Image will reflect more of a daytime camping experience. The colors incorporated will be geared towards a retro 70s throw back camping theme. 

**Night Mode:** this will be similar to "dark" mode. It will be a lighter background image. Image will reflect more of a nighttime camping experience. The colors incorporated will be neon colors, mimicking a music festival light show. 

NOTE: The placement and style of the button is TBD

When logging in and hitting the landing page (I think it actually does not matter what page comes after the login) I can go somewhere else (Hub, Q&V, does not matter) and when I go back I do hit the login page instead of the landing page (or whatever the start page was).

This is particularly problematic with the landing page because it has links in the text and the back button after hitting a link does not lead back to the link. Irritating.
